sess the detectability of GW signal, we also calculate the signal to noise\nratio (SNR), which are $\\rm SNR=37.7~ (66.5)$ and $27~(47.7)$ for $m_{\\rm x}=3$\nkeV and $m_{\\rm x}=1$ keV for Einstein Telescope (ET) with Salpeter (Chabrier)\nIMF, respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2016 02:13:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-28"}
