ecular outflow. The\nkinetic energy and radial momentum of the cold molecular phase of the outflow\ncorrespond to about 2% and 20%, respectively, of the supernovae output. The\ncold molecular outflow velocity is lower than the escape velocity, so the gas\nwill likely return to the galaxy disk. The mass loading factor is ~0.1-0.5, so\nthe negative feedback due to this star-formation powered molecular outflow is\nprobably limited.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2016 10:54:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-26"}
