n the mid-transit times of the hot Jupiter, caused\nby an Earth-sized planet in a 3:2 mean motion resonance. Analyzing the\nsynthetic light curves produced after certain epochs, we attempt to recover the\nsynthetically added TTV signal by means of usual primary transit fitting\ntechniques, and show how these can recover (or not) the TTV signal.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2016 11:29:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-14"}
