10^{13.5}{\\rm\ncm})^{0.55}~\\rm d$. The suppression of $L$ at $t_{\\rm tr}/a$ obtained for\nstandard polytropic envelopes may account for the first optical peak of\ndouble-peaked SN light curves, with first peak at a few days for $M_{\\rm\nenv}<1M_\\odot$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2016 12:33:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 5 Mar 2017 19:56:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-12"}
