 computes their effective temperatures using purely asteroseismic\nmethods. There are in general very close agreements between effective\ntemperatures from asteroseismic and non-asteroseismic (spectral and\nphotometric) methods. For the Sun and Procyon A, for example, the agreement is\nalmost total.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2016 14:33:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-24"}
